title: List of types of seafood
text:
The following is a list of types of seafood. <a href="Seafood">Seafood</a> is any form of <a href="sea%20life">sea life</a> regarded as <a href="food">food</a> by humans. It prominently includes <a href="Fish%20%28food%29">fish</a>, <a href="shellfish">shellfish</a>, and <a href="roe">roe</a>. Shellfish include various species of <a href="Mollusca">mollusc</a>s, <a href="crustacean">crustacean</a>s, and <a href="echinoderm">echinoderm</a>s. Historically, <a href="sea%20mammal">sea mammal</a>s such as whales and dolphins have been consumed as food, though that happens to a lesser extent in modern times. Edible sea plants, such as some <a href="Edible%20seaweed">seaweeds</a> and <a href="microalgae">microalgae</a>, are widely eaten as seafood around the world, especially in Asia (see the ). In <a href="North%20America">North America</a>, although not generally in the <a href="United%20Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>, the term "seafood" is extended to <a href="fresh%20water">fresh water</a> organisms eaten by humans, so any edible <a href="aquatic%20life">aquatic life</a> may be broadly referred to as seafood.
Echinoderms.
These are common in some Asian cuisines
Medusozoa.
Some species of <a href="jellyfish">jellyfish</a> are edible and used as a source of food.
Tunicates (sea squirts).
"<a href="Microcosmus%20sabatieri">Microcosmus sabatieri</a>", also known as sea fig or violet, is eaten in parts of Europe.
